You may recognise this little man whom I love to record on my stories and y‚Äôall probably sick of seeing him all the time. We also tend to wear hats outside so I guess we are crooked hats brothers.

His name is Alikhan  and he‚Äôs my cousin.
It was his third birthday already yesterday and I wish I could stay for his birthday. We do meet a few times per year  and one thing that never changes is that he keeps forgetting me. He‚Äôs almost always a pain in the butt  yet he‚Äôs the cutest kid in the world. Normally I‚Äôm not into kids but he‚Äôs sooo lovely that I can‚Äôt help but interact with him (honestly anyone would). Oh  and he‚Äôs also pretty smart for a 3 years old and is willing to fight anyone ‚úä‚úä.

Anyways  happy birthday kid. I guess I won‚Äôt see you for a couple of years  but next time I do  you‚Äôre gonna hide behind your mom  because you won‚Äôt remember me. And you‚Äôll be a big big hooligan. @guljike @aiaganovsabyrzhan @aza_ta_chernaya_jopa

We were supposed to take a nice picture together in May  during my graduation ceremony. But oh well  pandemic happened  and here we are  happily sipping tea at 3am at the airport  just before my flight to Philly. Dejected as we were  it was a sweet moment. There were so many sweet moments during the last half of the year.

Cannot help being annoyed with my derailed summer plans  but also somehow I am grateful. Pandemic did bring many people closer  in unexpected ways. I was overwhelmed with the amount of support I received from my friends and family  while in Singapore  at home  and as I am settling into Omerican life. I have felt uneasy during these times (& continue to do so)  but Alhamdullilah to my family  a constant presence in my life that comforts and guides me  regardless of how far we are. Love you mum and elder bro ‚ù§Ô∏èüòò.

Philly has been great so far; settling in anew sucks  but it‚Äôs a must-have expression. In 2 days here  I already went through a few adventures. Anyways  grad school starts on Monday  so I‚Äôll be focusing intensely on that. Apologies if it takes me a while to respond.
7am emails suck but 7pm sunsets are pretty good
Grateful to @adheper for ditching his Zaynebs of the world and agreeing to show me around Istanbul. Got to taste a pide that I wouldn‚Äôt taste anywhere else  and it was really good.

Had it not been for these two top lads from home  this semester would have been much more stressful and boring. Thanks for choosing YNC jigitterüí•üí•üí• And then there‚Äôs Krishna who loves to curse at me in my own languages üôÉüôÉüôÉ
Spasibo Misha for the cutest gift - in the midst of the hell I‚Äôm going through a smile surfaced on my face after watching this. –Ø —Ç–æ–∂–µ –±—É–¥—É —Å–∏–ª—å–Ω–æ —Å–∫—É—á–∞—Ç—å!

Hey Laura Apayka @bueau.almodovar thanks for blessing Singapore with your presence for the past 2.5 weeks. Sunsets literally started showing up when you came lolz.
So  one of my closest friends from home visited me in SG. I was glad that you got to experience this country: now I actually have someone who shares the pains and suffering and benefits of living here  so I guess that‚Äôs nice. I‚Äôm also proud that you did all the crazy things that you did here (though I expected nothing less from you my sensei)  so that‚Äôs cool too. A tough year is awaiting both of us  but in the meantime  I‚Äôm really grateful for the chocolate  conversations  jokes  having to take thousand and one photos of you  and cakes and coffees with you. I guess I am no longer that dumb kid I were when we first met (or am I? xD)  but it feels nice (and nostalgic) to be silly in your warm presence.

Happy New Year humans :) Hope that 2016 brought both sadness and joy  taught some good life lessons  & made us better human beings and 2017 will make us even better. Thanks to those from YNC who accepted and put up with my weird behavior (but alas there's much more to come) and mad props to my fellow classmates and friends who were always there to remind me my real self.
